1
00:00:07,507 --> 00:00:09,217
Everything is beautiful.

2
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:13,555
It's too beautiful.

3
00:00:15,348 --> 00:00:16,224
Yeah.

4
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:22,647
- Wow.
- Whoa.

5
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:24,649
This is nice.

6
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,151
It's so refined.

7
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:28,403
Refined is the only way to describe it.

8
00:00:28,486 --> 00:00:29,320
Yeah.

9
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:33,700
This tree is impressive too.

10
00:00:33,783 --> 00:00:34,784
Yeah, it is.

11
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:40,415
How cute.

12
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:42,584
Wow.

13
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:44,169
It's so lovely.

14
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:45,295
Yeah.

15
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:55,430
Our room is Araragi.

16
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:57,432
- Araragi.
- Where is it?

17
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,104
I see it.

18
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:04,397
Here it is.

19
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:11,946
Let's go in.

20
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,449
Wow, this is amazing.

21
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:16,201
Wow.

22
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:17,827
This is great!

23
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:23,291
That's the tree we just saw.

24
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:26,085
This is really amazing.

25
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:27,670
- Yeah, it's so nice.
- Yeah.

26
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:31,341
Want to go to the onsen?

27
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:34,135
Or do you want to take a walk?

28
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:36,679
- Let's enjoy the onsen first.
- Okay.

29
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:39,557
I'm ready to relax already.

30
00:01:39,641 --> 00:01:41,226
Yeah, we're here to relax.

31
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:42,185
Yeah.

32
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:44,646
Wow.

33
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,148
This is the best.

34
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:48,358
Let's walk later on.

35
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:49,442
Yeah, let's.

36
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:28,231
What?

37
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:31,276
- Oh.
- Did you find ice cream?

38
00:02:31,359 --> 00:02:33,319
No, ball-shaped konjac.

39
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:35,113
It's usually only eaten at a hot spring.

40
00:02:35,196 --> 00:02:38,366
- You're right.
- Then I'll get ice cream.

41
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:40,451
This conversation
is going all over the place.

42
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:53,214
Beer and ice cream, huh?

43
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,635
Having beer and ice cream feels like…

44
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:58,803
What?

45
00:02:59,429 --> 00:03:00,972
Like I'm spoiling myself.

46
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:03,808
It's like you're both
an adult and a child.

47
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:05,268
Yeah.

48
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:10,565
But you know…

49
00:03:11,691 --> 00:03:13,109
I'm freezing.

50
00:03:13,192 --> 00:03:16,154
That's why I told you to get
the ball-shaped konjac instead.

51
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:21,200
- But I want alcohol after the onsen.
- That's why I told you to get <i>amazake</i>.

52
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:22,952
- I'm freezing.
- You look cold.

53
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:25,246
- But it's delicious.
- I'm glad to hear that.

54
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:31,377
Oh look.

55
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,352
It's so fluffy.

56
00:03:47,435 --> 00:03:49,395
Look how fluffy it is.

57
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,439
So fluffy.

58
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:53,650
- May I pet him?
- Sure.

59
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,443
Hey there.

60
00:03:55,526 --> 00:03:57,070
- What's his name?
- Milk.

61
00:03:57,153 --> 00:03:57,987
Milk.

62
00:03:58,071 --> 00:03:59,822
Milk. So cute.

63
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,493
- He's so warm.
- So fluffy.

64
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:05,578
He's so fluffy.

65
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:07,497
Yeah, he's really fluffy, huh?

66
00:04:08,122 --> 00:04:10,541
Look at this fluffy fur!

67
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:13,962
So cute.

68
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:15,296
He's too cute.

69
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:17,966
So cute.

70
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:18,967
It's so soft.

71
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:21,928
He's so gentle too.

72
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:38,444
It's good.

73
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:44,867
You know,

74
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:49,747
whenever I see this, I realize
that I'm really at an onsen.

75
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:53,960
- This? This flame?
- Yeah.

76
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:57,797
People who normally eat
Japanese multi-course meals like this

77
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:00,049
might not feel the same way,

78
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:05,596
but when I see this mysterious
blue solid fuel,

79
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,557
it makes me think, "I'm at an onsen."

80
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:09,934
I realize I'm really on a vacation.

81
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:12,145
That's what makes you think of the onsen?

82
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:37,128
You know,

83
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:41,090
people become silent when eating, right?

84
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,010
Yeah, because they're eating.

85
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:46,888
It's because they're using
their mouth to eat, right?

86
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:49,057
Yeah.

87
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:53,686
The mouth
is used for both eating and speaking.

88
00:05:54,937 --> 00:05:58,900
The ears are only used for hearing,
and the eyes are only used for seeing.

89
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:01,903
You're right.

90
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,780
The mouth is used for breathing too.

91
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:06,365
A lot of strain is placed on the mouth.

92
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:09,410
Okay, then…

93
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:14,040
Would it have been better

94
00:06:14,123 --> 00:06:17,001
if breathing, eating, and speaking

95
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,630
were all separated by their own organ?

96
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:26,135
I think it's fine for one organ to be
in charge of both breathing and eating,

97
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:28,471
but maybe speaking could've been separate.

98
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:32,767
Then where would be a good spot?

99
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,560
- What?
- Where could it go?

100
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:37,647
Here?

101
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:46,614
This Japanese sake is so good,
but it's a little sweet.

102
00:06:57,834 --> 00:07:00,670
But if it's here, I'm afraid
spit would come running down my face.

103
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:02,004
But…

104
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:08,261
If you don't eat or breathe through here,

105
00:07:08,344 --> 00:07:10,012
there's no need for saliva, right?

106
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:13,474
You need saliva, just not teeth.

107
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:16,310
Really? I think you need teeth instead.

108
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:18,187
Because if you have no teeth,

109
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,982
you'll end up talking like this.

110
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:24,026
Right.

111
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,528
So teeth are necessary.

112
00:07:27,488 --> 00:07:29,824
That means we'll have to brush our teeth.

113
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:32,243
That means spit and stuff
will be coming down your face.

114
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:37,165
Then is this a bad location?

115
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:40,585
How about here?

116
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:42,753
That's the same spot as the mouth.

117
00:07:44,422 --> 00:07:47,133
Oh I got it! I'm a genius!

118
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:49,469
Let me explain.

119
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:51,804
- Stay quiet and just listen.
- What the heck?

120
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:53,181
- I haven't said anything.
- Quiet.

121
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:55,057
Tell me where.

122
00:07:56,017 --> 00:07:57,059
Here.

123
00:07:58,019 --> 00:07:58,978
See?

124
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,980
We have one eye, one nose,

125
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:03,524
and one mouth, but two ears.

126
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:06,736
So why not turn one of the ears

127
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:08,571
into a mouth for speaking?

128
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:09,989
Hey, hey.

129
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:12,533
Yukio, you only have one eye?

130
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:17,079
We have two eyes, huh?

131
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:20,458
My idea wasn't so great after all.

132
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:25,254
Hey, stop getting all excited
and sad all on your own.

133
00:08:28,841 --> 00:08:29,800
But you know,

134
00:08:31,093 --> 00:08:32,470
I think I've got it.

135
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:35,973
- Got what?
- We only need one mouth after all.

136
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:37,642
I'm not ready to give up yet.

137
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:40,520
Sorry, it was my fault
for bringing up this subject.

138
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:42,104
Let's eat before our food gets cold.

139
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:45,399
But we were so close
to figuring out an answer.

140
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:47,568
If only we didn't have two eyes.

141
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:51,948
Even if we only had one eye,
speaking with the ear would be weird.

142
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,034
Why?

143
00:08:58,454 --> 00:08:59,497
Come here.

144
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:03,834
Come here.

145
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:06,837
What is it?

146
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:08,548
- Here?
- Yeah.

147
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,926
If my right ear was used for listening,

148
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:14,971
and the left ear was a mouth for speaking,
it would be like this.

149
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,180
Say something.

150
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:18,641
Okay.

151
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,478
You look good in that <i>yukata</i>.
You're so cute.

152
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:27,858
Really? I'm happy to hear that.

153
00:09:34,198 --> 00:09:37,994
Seeing these flames makes me realize
that I'm really at a hot spring inn.

154
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:42,915
The flame?

155
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:47,837
The flame.

156
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:53,467
That's what reminds you of the onsen?
See how silly it is?

157
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:54,802
It's as if we're dancing.

158
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,429
It would be too much work.

159
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:57,597
We'd need space too.

160
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,640
Hold on. I've got it. Come this way.

161
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:02,893
- What is it?
- If we go like this,

162
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:06,022
we won't have to move around that much
to converse.

163
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:07,273
Say something.

164
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:08,649
- Ready?
- Yeah.

165
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:12,153
What's your new idea, Yukio?

166
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:18,534
If we turn around, we can converse
without moving around so much.

167
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:23,039
You're right.
It doesn't require much movement.

168
00:10:23,831 --> 00:10:24,790
Right?

169
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:27,793
But can I point something out?

170
00:10:28,836 --> 00:10:29,712
What is it?

171
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:33,257
This is a bit hectic too.

172
00:10:33,341 --> 00:10:34,383
You're right.

173
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:37,970
Let's eat.

174
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:41,390
Getting up and fooling around
during a meal is bad manners.

175
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:43,309
You're absolutely right.

176
00:10:44,101 --> 00:10:45,394
That didn't work, huh?

177
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:54,737
Why are you laughing?

178
00:10:55,821 --> 00:10:58,491
I was thinking of how you're such a dummy.

179
00:10:58,574 --> 00:10:59,659
What?

180
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:03,829
You're the one who started saying

181
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:04,997
- that the mouth is--
- Gross.

182
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:07,416
- Don't talk with your mouth full.
- Shut up.

183
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:14,256
Let's take another bath after we eat.

184
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:17,885
Sure.

185
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:40,282
It's a ping pong table.

186
00:11:40,866 --> 00:11:41,867
Want to play?

187
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:45,746
I just took a bath. I don't want to sweat.

188
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:55,464
I'm really bad at ping pong.

189
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:56,882
As for me,

190
00:11:56,966 --> 00:12:00,302
I played in a club in elementary school,
so I think I'll be pretty good.

191
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:03,305
Hold on.

192
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:05,808
- Ready?
- Yeah.

193
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:10,396
- That was a good serve.
- Not really.

194
00:12:10,479 --> 00:12:11,647
It wasn't?

195
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:14,024
It's okay, try again.

196
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,029
- Ready?
- Okay.

197
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:22,366
Take that.

198
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:24,326
Nice.

199
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,412
- So…
- Yeah?

200
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:30,541
When you serve, you have to let the ball
bounce once on your side of the net,

201
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:31,625
and again on the other side.

202
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:33,544
Oh, it needs to bounce.

203
00:12:33,627 --> 00:12:34,837
Yeah. Like this.

204
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:37,590
Hold on.

205
00:12:41,343 --> 00:12:43,429
- It's so hard.
- This is going nowhere.

206
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:46,515
- Again.
- Okay.

207
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:49,018
This is hard.

208
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:53,439
- Are you serious?
- No.

209
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:56,525
It's hard to figure out
how much force to use.

210
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:01,113
I can hit anywhere on the table?

211
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,406
- Yeah.
- Okay.

212
00:13:04,033 --> 00:13:05,493
This is good, right?

213
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:07,453
- Not exactly.
- Why?

214
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:08,954
- It's a little off.
- What do you mean?

215
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:10,498
You only let it bounce on your side

216
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:11,540
when you're serving.

217
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:13,876
Oh I see. Just once?

218
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,211
Yeah, just the first time.

219
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:16,253
Like this.

220
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:19,215
- Then I do this?
- Yeah, kind of.

221
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:22,051
Here.

222
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:24,637
I let it bounce once, right?

223
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:28,599
- Nice.
- I did it.

224
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:49,453
What is it?

225
00:13:50,371 --> 00:13:52,164
You sucked at ping pong.

226
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:54,542
That's why I told you I'm not good at it.

227
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,919
How are you that bad?

228
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:58,420
Do you suck at all sports?

229
00:13:59,296 --> 00:14:02,007
I'm not making fun of you.

230
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:04,343
I'm not bad at all sports.

231
00:14:04,426 --> 00:14:07,513
It's just ping pong.
I'm especially bad at it.

232
00:14:09,431 --> 00:14:11,392
The ping pong ball is too light.

233
00:14:11,475 --> 00:14:13,936
I don't understand why it's so light.
It's a one yen coin.

234
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:16,230
It's heavier than a one yen coin.

235
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:21,777
I've never met someone who's annoyed
because the ping pong ball is too light.

236
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:23,988
If the ball weighed as much as this,

237
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:26,365
- I'd be able to play pretty well.
- No way.

238
00:14:26,448 --> 00:14:29,326
- That ball is too light.
- It would break your wrist.

239
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:33,330
Then does that mean you're good
at bowling?

240
00:14:34,582 --> 00:14:38,210
My ball always falls in the gutter.
Those balls are too heavy.

241
00:14:39,253 --> 00:14:41,672
It's heavy enough to kill someone
if it hits their head.

242
00:14:41,755 --> 00:14:44,216
It's a lethal weapon.
And it ruins my nails.

243
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,427
You're just full of complaints.

244
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:55,394
Let's play again once they finish.

245
00:14:55,477 --> 00:14:58,022
- No, I will not.
- Oh!

246
00:14:58,606 --> 00:14:59,690
That scared me.

247
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:00,900
Sorry.

248
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,568
Thank you.

249
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:07,406
It's dangerous.

250
00:15:07,948 --> 00:15:10,743
You're scared of the ball now?

251
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:11,994
I'm not scared.

252
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:21,795
Sorry.

253
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:23,881
- It's all right.
- Be careful.

254
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:24,798
Thank you.

255
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:27,009
No worries.

256
00:15:27,801 --> 00:15:29,929
I can't believe you told him
to be careful.

257
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:55,663
Good night.

258
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:39,058
<i>Encounters are a strange concept,</i>
<i>aren't they?</i>

259
00:17:39,641 --> 00:17:40,726
<i>Encounters?</i>

260
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,648
Yeah, I was thinking about it yesterday.

261
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:50,736
Late at night,
at a convenience store in my neighborhood,

262
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:52,946
the same two people are always
at the register.

263
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:57,159
I don't know which country
either of them are from.

264
00:17:58,285 --> 00:17:59,912
They're probably from different countries.

265
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:03,457
- A man and a woman?
- Yeah.

266
00:18:05,542 --> 00:18:08,337
Well, it's not particularly unusual,

267
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:11,465
and it's an everyday scene
that can be found anywhere.

268
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:17,846
But when they were born,
they never imagined they'd ever meet.

269
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,390
But they happened to meet

270
00:18:20,474 --> 00:18:23,727
and work at the same convenience store
in Japan.

271
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,107
After working there for a year,

272
00:18:28,732 --> 00:18:31,485
depending on their shifts,

273
00:18:31,568 --> 00:18:34,238
they'll end up spending
a fair amount of time together.

274
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:41,161
It's interesting.

275
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:43,997
I find it so fascinating.

276
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,835
What exactly is an encounter?

277
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:55,592
That's something that's happening
in all convenience stores.

278
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:56,510
Yeah.

279
00:18:57,094 --> 00:19:00,139
It's the same with elementary
and middle schools.

280
00:19:00,722 --> 00:19:04,017
You encounter certain people
because you all happened to live nearby.

281
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:10,691
Speaking of which,
I was reading it while back in university.

282
00:19:10,774 --> 00:19:12,151
Reading what?

283
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:13,735
Your novels.

284
00:19:16,738 --> 00:19:19,449
So our relationship
is quite fascinating as well.

285
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:22,911
At least to me, it is.

286
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:23,912
I guess so.

287
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:35,174
How did you meet your current boyfriend?

288
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:38,051
You want to know?

289
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:43,807
It's kind of funny, actually.

290
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:46,518
We met at a local laundromat.

291
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:47,936
- A laundromat?
- Yeah.

292
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:53,192
He's a hairstylist,

293
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:57,696
and it just so happened that his salon's
washing machine broke down that day.

294
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:00,866
I use the laundromat from time to time,

295
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:02,284
but yeah,

296
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:06,371
he happened to be there washing
a large amount of towels for his salon.

297
00:20:06,455 --> 00:20:07,414
I see.

298
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:13,754
I was listening to music with my earphones
but the sound was leaking.

299
00:20:13,837 --> 00:20:16,715
He noticed that,
and initiated a conversation with me.

300
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:17,966
That's how it started.

301
00:20:21,261 --> 00:20:23,305
If his washing machine hadn't broken down…

302
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:26,016
We wouldn't have met.

303
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,813
If my music wasn't leaking
from my earphones…

304
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,150
Then you wouldn't be with him right now.

305
00:20:41,114 --> 00:20:42,699
Are you glad you met him?

306
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:47,412
Yeah. I'm glad.

307
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:49,081
I see.

308
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,961
What about him?

309
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:00,759
I have no way of knowing that.

310
00:21:04,888 --> 00:21:06,348
<i>Since I'm not him.</i>

311
00:22:55,999 --> 00:22:57,209
You're awake?

312
00:22:57,959 --> 00:22:59,044
Good morning.

313
00:22:59,127 --> 00:23:00,128
Good morning.

314
00:23:02,964 --> 00:23:05,217
We came here to relax,
but we're up already.

315
00:23:08,637 --> 00:23:09,846
Yeah.

316
00:23:12,015 --> 00:23:13,767
You want to go back to sleep?
Or some coffee?

317
00:23:15,393 --> 00:23:16,645
Or to eat breakfast?

318
00:23:19,147 --> 00:23:20,357
I'll have coffee.

319
00:23:21,191 --> 00:23:22,818
I don't need breakfast.

320
00:23:23,318 --> 00:23:26,279
You can go eat breakfast.
Don't worry about me.

321
00:23:28,281 --> 00:23:30,033
I think coffee will be good enough.

322
00:23:44,005 --> 00:23:46,049
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

323
00:24:07,362 --> 00:24:10,448
For you. Happy birthday.

324
00:24:10,532 --> 00:24:11,700
Thank you.

325
00:24:14,744 --> 00:24:16,371
- Can I open it?
- Of course.

326
00:24:18,039 --> 00:24:19,416
Is it clothes?

327
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:28,300
It's so cute!

328
00:24:31,678 --> 00:24:33,180
- Can I try it on?
- Yeah.

329
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:07,672
What do you think?

330
00:25:07,756 --> 00:25:08,882
It suits you.

331
00:25:11,635 --> 00:25:12,761
It's cute.

332
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:15,013
You kept the <i>yukata</i> on?

333
00:25:15,847 --> 00:25:17,432
Should I have changed out of it?

334
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:19,100
It's okay.

335
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:22,854
Oh, this color.

336
00:25:24,856 --> 00:25:27,442
The color that makes you realize
you're at an onsen.

337
00:25:28,652 --> 00:25:30,528
You're right. It's onsen blue.

338
00:25:31,112 --> 00:25:33,823
Onsen blue? That sounds lame.

339
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,286
Ayana?

340
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:42,290
- You know…
- What is it?

341
00:25:42,958 --> 00:25:44,876
There's something I want.

342
00:25:45,877 --> 00:25:47,045
For my birthday.

343
00:25:48,213 --> 00:25:49,297
What is it?

344
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:52,550
Can you knit me a scarf?

345
00:25:52,634 --> 00:25:53,551
A scarf?

346
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:58,932
It's a lot of work, huh?
It's okay if you can't.

347
00:25:59,891 --> 00:26:01,476
I just kind of wanted one.

348
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:05,105
I can knit you a scarf no problem.
But why all of a sudden?

349
00:26:06,231 --> 00:26:07,190
Why?

350
00:26:09,234 --> 00:26:13,488
I just wanted a new scarf, that's all.

351
00:26:15,615 --> 00:26:18,910
But winter will be over by then.
Your birthday is in March.

352
00:26:19,411 --> 00:26:21,413
That's true, but…

353
00:26:23,581 --> 00:26:26,084
Okay, I'll make it for you.

354
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:30,338
In fact, I can finish making it
before your birthday.

355
00:26:30,839 --> 00:26:32,507
Do you want it earlier?

356
00:26:34,968 --> 00:26:38,013
Really? But it's okay,
I'll wait until my birthday.

357
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:39,973
Okay.

358
00:26:44,436 --> 00:26:46,354
We're not in a rush this morning, right?

359
00:26:47,522 --> 00:26:48,565
Mind if I go in the onsen?

360
00:27:34,903 --> 00:27:38,948
WHITE DOG, COLD HANDS,
LIGHT BLUE, LONG BANGS

361
00:27:39,532 --> 00:27:42,243
THE PRESENT WILL SOON BE THE PAST

362
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:45,455
EVEN THOUGH THE PAST WILL REMAIN THE PAST

363
00:28:44,639 --> 00:28:46,683
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

364
00:29:13,710 --> 00:29:15,503
Onsen blue.

365
00:29:20,842 --> 00:29:21,885
Excuse me.

366
00:29:57,545 --> 00:29:59,005
This is the worst.

367
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:11,661
Coming.

368
00:31:23,965 --> 00:31:26,050
- Hey.
- Hey.

369
00:31:28,303 --> 00:31:29,470
You look sickly.

370
00:31:30,597 --> 00:31:31,890
I am sick.

371
00:31:38,771 --> 00:31:40,273
Thanks for calling me over.

372
00:31:40,356 --> 00:31:41,399
Sure.

373
00:31:46,738 --> 00:31:47,822
Did you eat something?

374
00:31:49,741 --> 00:31:51,075
I bought Jell-O and stuff.

375
00:31:52,118 --> 00:31:53,286
Thank you.

376
00:31:54,537 --> 00:31:55,788
But I'll pass for now.

377
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:00,627
Then I'll have some.

378
00:32:01,794 --> 00:32:03,922
You bought one for yourself too?

379
00:32:04,005 --> 00:32:04,964
Yeah.

380
00:32:06,299 --> 00:32:08,051
Then can I have just one bite of yours?

381
00:32:23,524 --> 00:32:24,359
Here.

382
00:32:28,738 --> 00:32:29,864
It's good.

383
00:32:30,406 --> 00:32:31,282
You like it?

384
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:34,202
I want the whole thing.

385
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:36,746
No, yours is in the fridge.

386
00:32:36,829 --> 00:32:37,872
This one is mine.

387
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:41,084
Stingy.

388
00:32:48,633 --> 00:32:50,259
How was the onsen trip?

389
00:32:51,094 --> 00:32:52,178
The onsen?

390
00:32:54,722 --> 00:32:56,057
It was awesome.

391
00:32:57,475 --> 00:33:00,687
The onsen was amazing,
and the food was delicious.

392
00:33:02,146 --> 00:33:05,692
- Ikaho, was it?
- Yeah, Ikaho.

393
00:33:11,531 --> 00:33:13,574
You don't seem too interested
in onsen and stuff.

394
00:33:14,367 --> 00:33:15,410
Yeah.

395
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:18,913
I know it's fun once you're there.

396
00:33:20,123 --> 00:33:22,333
But I don't really want to go anywhere.

397
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:26,129
I can tell.

398
00:33:29,340 --> 00:33:33,845
- You're a boring person after all.
- Yup, a boring person.

399
00:33:39,517 --> 00:33:40,977
Give me a bite.

400
00:33:41,477 --> 00:33:43,855
Just go get your own from the fridge.

401
00:33:43,938 --> 00:33:46,899
I don't want to. It's a hassle to get up.

402
00:33:58,494 --> 00:33:59,370
What is it?

403
00:34:01,330 --> 00:34:02,415
What's what?

404
00:34:05,084 --> 00:34:08,046
What is it?
Did something happen with your boyfriend?

405
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:16,596
You called me here because you wanted
to talk about it, right?

406
00:34:22,351 --> 00:34:24,395
That's what caused your fever, right?

407
00:34:25,104 --> 00:34:27,523
You were probably thinking too much
and got sick.

408
00:34:28,608 --> 00:34:30,735
You're not the type of person
who catches colds.

409
00:34:32,236 --> 00:34:35,406
- I'm too dumb to get sick?
- Yeah, because you're dumb.

410
00:34:37,241 --> 00:34:38,201
You're so mean.

411
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:42,246
I really have a cold. I'm coughing too.

412
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:43,539
- Really?
- Yeah.

413
00:34:44,499 --> 00:34:48,127
But if everything was fine with
your boyfriend, he'd be here right now.

414
00:35:11,275 --> 00:35:12,985
- Hey.
- Yeah?

415
00:35:17,156 --> 00:35:18,157
What is it?

416
00:35:24,580 --> 00:35:25,498
Well…

417
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:35,883
Let's stop meeting each other like this.

418
00:35:38,845 --> 00:35:40,221
Can we please end it?

419
00:35:59,448 --> 00:36:00,700
Can I ask

420
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:04,704
for the reason why?

421
00:36:07,915 --> 00:36:10,084
Hey, that's my Jell-O!

422
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:13,254
I'm taking a bite from yours
since you took a bite of mine.

423
00:36:13,337 --> 00:36:15,256
I just took what I gave to you.

424
00:36:25,725 --> 00:36:26,559
Here you go.

425
00:36:27,476 --> 00:36:28,686
Hold on.

426
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:32,106
Use this.

427
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:34,025
Thanks.

428
00:36:34,108 --> 00:36:35,693
- Is that okay?
- Thanks.

429
00:36:57,256 --> 00:36:58,549
I had fun.

430
00:37:00,426 --> 00:37:01,260
What?

431
00:37:03,471 --> 00:37:07,058
The trip was a lot of fun.

432
00:37:07,558 --> 00:37:08,392
I see.

433
00:37:17,860 --> 00:37:19,320
We arrived at the inn,

434
00:37:20,863 --> 00:37:22,240
and enjoyed the onsen.

435
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:27,036
Then we took a walk together.

436
00:37:31,165 --> 00:37:34,460
During the walk,

437
00:37:36,128 --> 00:37:40,383
there was a big white dog
at an open square.

438
00:37:41,759 --> 00:37:43,970
A group of children
were gathered around it.

439
00:37:45,054 --> 00:37:46,764
The fluffy type of dog?

440
00:37:46,847 --> 00:37:47,807
Yeah.

441
00:37:48,766 --> 00:37:49,976
A big dog.

442
00:37:53,229 --> 00:37:54,105
And then?

443
00:37:56,357 --> 00:37:57,525
And then,

444
00:37:59,151 --> 00:38:04,031
he saw the dog and ran towards it
with a big smile on his face.

445
00:38:06,701 --> 00:38:08,786
He joined the kids,

446
00:38:10,413 --> 00:38:13,791
and was having so much fun
petting the dog.

447
00:38:18,587 --> 00:38:20,339
When I saw that,

448
00:38:26,637 --> 00:38:27,930
I got kind of scared.

449
00:38:34,937 --> 00:38:36,814
I felt calm.

450
00:38:38,774 --> 00:38:40,359
During the entire trip.

451
00:38:44,655 --> 00:38:47,408
I was really enjoying myself.

452
00:38:49,994 --> 00:38:51,620
It was relaxing in a good way.

453
00:38:58,836 --> 00:39:00,546
I know it's too late now,

454
00:39:04,425 --> 00:39:05,676
but

455
00:39:07,970 --> 00:39:11,265
I realized that I don't want
to betray him anymore.

456
00:39:14,727 --> 00:39:15,686
Yeah.

457
00:39:17,897 --> 00:39:19,315
That's all.

458
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:34,246
He's precious to me.

459
00:39:37,291 --> 00:39:38,459
Very much so.

460
00:39:44,006 --> 00:39:45,674
Lying to him is painful.

461
00:39:53,307 --> 00:39:55,434
I want to straighten myself out.

462
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:57,895
To clean up my act.

463
00:40:00,689 --> 00:40:01,982
I want to do things right.

464
00:40:05,111 --> 00:40:07,905
I might not be able to do it,
but I want to give it a try.

465
00:40:15,204 --> 00:40:16,997
I'm saying this now,

466
00:40:19,667 --> 00:40:21,502
but I might not be able to do it.

467
00:40:25,881 --> 00:40:28,884
I might get attracted to someone else
very quickly,

468
00:40:30,219 --> 00:40:33,556
or it might not be possible for me

469
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:38,519
to cherish just one person
for the rest of my life.

470
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,691
I'm aware of all that.

471
00:40:47,027 --> 00:40:48,779
I know that, but still…

472
00:40:51,907 --> 00:40:53,659
But I still want to try.

473
00:40:57,663 --> 00:40:59,623
I want to face him with honesty.

474
00:41:09,425 --> 00:41:10,509
What do you think?

475
00:41:18,934 --> 00:41:20,853
I think…

476
00:41:24,315 --> 00:41:26,525
that'd be a wonderful thing to do, but…

477
00:41:29,820 --> 00:41:30,821
But what?

478
00:41:35,743 --> 00:41:36,952
I'm worried.

479
00:41:40,331 --> 00:41:41,373
Worried?

480
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:46,462
I'm a little worried.

481
00:41:49,089 --> 00:41:51,008
What do you mean you're worried?

482
00:41:52,718 --> 00:41:53,719
Well,

483
00:41:54,929 --> 00:41:57,598
I'm fine ending things
as long as you're going to be okay.

484
00:41:58,307 --> 00:41:59,433
But

485
00:42:02,102 --> 00:42:03,354
I was wondering

486
00:42:04,396 --> 00:42:07,441
if things will get difficult for you
from now on.

487
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:13,447
There was a part of you

488
00:42:14,740 --> 00:42:17,284
that found relief
by confiding everything in me, right?

489
00:42:20,287 --> 00:42:23,916
Although that goes for me too.

490
00:42:30,381 --> 00:42:32,258
Should I not have kissed you?

491
00:42:33,300 --> 00:42:36,971
Is that what ended up causing you pain?

492
00:42:37,471 --> 00:42:39,014
No, that's not it.

493
00:42:42,184 --> 00:42:43,018
You know,

494
00:42:44,270 --> 00:42:47,022
our relationship right now
is kind of weird.

495
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:51,193
We've kissed,
but we've never slept together.

496
00:42:52,861 --> 00:42:54,196
How can I say this…?

497
00:42:56,156 --> 00:43:00,703
To be honest, there's a part of me
that doesn't care

498
00:43:01,996 --> 00:43:04,748
whether we sleep together or not.

499
00:43:04,832 --> 00:43:06,917
It doesn't matter if we do it or not.

500
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:13,007
But at the same time, I'm scared
of passing the point of no return.

501
00:43:20,014 --> 00:43:25,019
If we decide

502
00:43:26,729 --> 00:43:29,231
never to touch each other anymore,

503
00:43:30,941 --> 00:43:34,695
will we be able to meet up again?

504
00:43:50,502 --> 00:43:52,046
I don't think so.

505
00:43:54,506 --> 00:43:55,966
We can't, huh.

506
00:43:57,468 --> 00:43:58,469
Yeah.

507
00:44:01,305 --> 00:44:03,807
Why?

508
00:44:09,772 --> 00:44:10,898
Because…

509
00:44:17,655 --> 00:44:18,822
It's because…

510
00:44:24,203 --> 00:44:26,580
I like you.

511
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:35,923
Because I don't want to lose you.

512
00:44:41,595 --> 00:44:44,682
And that's why from now on,

513
00:44:46,266 --> 00:44:48,560
we might meet for work related things,

514
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:51,897
but I want to stop meeting together
like this.

515
00:44:53,190 --> 00:44:54,525
I know I'm being selfish.

516
00:45:04,535 --> 00:45:06,912
Is it too selfish of me?

517
00:45:11,208 --> 00:45:12,126
No.

518
00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:16,630
Not at all.

519
00:45:19,842 --> 00:45:25,013
I completely understand.

520
00:45:39,903 --> 00:45:41,447
If that's what you want,

521
00:45:43,615 --> 00:45:46,535
I won't see you anymore.

522
00:45:49,913 --> 00:45:51,248
I won't contact you either.

523
00:46:11,310 --> 00:46:13,604
- Just one thing.
- What is it?

524
00:46:14,354 --> 00:46:16,106
Can I ask for one selfish request?

525
00:46:17,649 --> 00:46:18,525
What is it?

526
00:46:19,735 --> 00:46:22,029
Can I stay here until you fall asleep?

527
00:46:23,030 --> 00:46:25,782
I've always wanted to see
your sleeping face, just once.

528
00:46:26,533 --> 00:46:27,659
Oh jeez.

529
00:46:36,084 --> 00:46:39,379
I'm probably going to look super ugly,
but fine, if that's what you want.

530
00:46:48,514 --> 00:46:50,474
Hurry up and go to sleep.

531
00:46:51,934 --> 00:46:52,851
Shut up.

532
00:47:00,859 --> 00:47:02,027
Good night.

533
00:47:04,613 --> 00:47:05,822
Good night.

534
00:47:15,249 --> 00:47:17,918
<i>I watched him run up to the big white dog,</i>

535
00:47:18,627 --> 00:47:20,796
<i>and join the random group of kids</i>

536
00:47:21,922 --> 00:47:26,051
<i>to pet the dog's soft, fluffy fur,</i>

537
00:47:27,302 --> 00:47:29,972
<i>fully enjoying himself</i>
<i>with a big smile on his face.</i>

538
00:47:30,847 --> 00:47:33,934
<i>As I sat there in the cold</i>

539
00:47:34,017 --> 00:47:36,687
<i>with my beer and ice cream</i>
<i>that was about to melt,</i>

540
00:47:37,771 --> 00:47:40,816
<i>I found myself wanting to know</i>
<i>more and more about him.</i>

541
00:47:43,402 --> 00:47:45,821
<i>I realized how much I liked him.</i>

542
00:47:47,948 --> 00:47:50,492
<i>But for some reason,</i>

543
00:47:52,703 --> 00:47:57,165
<i>at the same time,</i>
<i>I felt like it was all too late.</i>

544
00:47:59,668 --> 00:48:02,212
<i>I felt like it was too late</i>
<i>for everything.</i>

545
00:48:05,465 --> 00:48:07,092
<i>My existence.</i>

546
00:48:08,802 --> 00:48:10,262
<i>The lies I'm holding onto.</i>

547
00:48:13,807 --> 00:48:18,103
<i>It all seemed so ugly,</i>

548
00:48:20,188 --> 00:48:23,859
<i>it almost felt like his only flaw was me.</i>

549
00:48:25,319 --> 00:48:29,197
<i>We're technically just strangers.</i>
<i>So even more so, I feel the guilt.</i>

550
00:48:31,617 --> 00:48:35,287
<i>There were moments when I wanted</i>
<i>to tell him the entire truth,</i>

551
00:48:35,954 --> 00:48:37,956
<i>but I could never do that.</i>

552
00:48:39,166 --> 00:48:41,126
<i>Because I don't like him that much.</i>

553
00:48:42,711 --> 00:48:46,089
<i>No, it's because I like him very much.</i>

554
00:48:48,675 --> 00:48:51,094
<i>He ran to the dog with such speed</i>

555
00:48:51,178 --> 00:48:54,181
<i>and innocence</i>
<i>that caused a fluttering of the wind.</i>

556
00:48:55,140 --> 00:48:58,435
<i>As I was left behind,</i>
<i>holding onto something cold in my hands,</i>

557
00:48:59,519 --> 00:49:02,314
<i>the fleeting encounter with</i>
<i>his quick departure felt like an eternity.</i>

558
00:49:04,691 --> 00:49:08,320
<i>It was an eternal separation</i>
<i>that felt like an instant.</i>

559
00:49:33,428 --> 00:49:34,346
What?

560
00:49:36,390 --> 00:49:37,974
Ayana.

561
00:49:43,605 --> 00:49:44,523
Oh.

562
00:49:44,606 --> 00:49:46,024
THIS DRAMA IS FICTIONAL

563
00:49:46,108 --> 00:49:46,983
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
